This paper deals with feedback control for multiantenna beamforming in wireless communication systems. The paper focuses on optimizing the feedback rate to maximize throughput while minimizing overhead. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also uses dynamic programming to compute the optimal control policy, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the effect of quantization on feedback, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
